<subSubSection id="FACCB3F919BD67AB56E28C4C5D8F4E7C" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="061C531E9911353DC04564925766D150" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0656C47520247DC5BABFF4EC38660FEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Medium sized (7.8-9.2 mm), dark species with olive-brown reflection; antennae dark; legs mostly black; body pile predominantly pale, except few black pile on vertex and scutum; basoflagellomere elongated (1.8 times as long as wide) obviously concave dorsally, arista 1.8 times as long as basoflagellomere (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D6B36271F5E7E9706715F448D550D108" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Antenna. A Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon bequaerti, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, female D Merodon sacki, outer side, lateral view, male E Merodon sacki, inner side, lateral view, male F Merodon sacki, dorsal view, male G Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, male H Merodon sophron, inner side, lateral view, male I Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377372" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">11G-I</figureCitation>
); tergum 2 with pale lateral maculae; metafemur incrassate with 
<taxonomicName id="373E922CD5B31EA61422C719ADAEC655" authorityName="Vujic, Likov &amp; Radenkovic" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="medium" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medium">medium</taxonomicName>
long pile on ventral surface, length approximately one third of its width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B1D12AAB1EF8BD835DECC0FFAAEC4CE0" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Metaleg, lateral view. A Merodon bequaerti, male B Merodon bequaerti, female C Merodon sacki, male D Merodon sophron, male. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377369" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">8D</figureCitation>
); male genitalia: posterior surstyle lobe with lateral hump; apical part of anterior surstyle lobe rhomboid; lingula 
<taxonomicName id="BC9D166B82C7D61FE58BD9A2F8CA61EA" authorityName="Vujic, Likov &amp; Radenkovic" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="medium" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medium">medium</taxonomicName>
size (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CFBF606A60DFEAB1F8745F0474EAAB5A" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9G-I</figureCitation>
). Related to 
<taxonomicName id="2AD729AA80D7CE5C4B8AA4D793F61484" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann in Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon serrulatus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis id="8DFD3339E7D1BE5054EE5E80E1A43090" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Merodon serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which differs in absence of medial fossette (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6807FC71548E88DC66939314B4CF5487" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Antenna. A Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon bequaerti, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, female D Merodon sacki, outer side, lateral view, male E Merodon sacki, inner side, lateral view, male F Merodon sacki, dorsal view, male G Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, male H Merodon sophron, inner side, lateral view, male I Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377372" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">11H</figureCitation>
), present in geographically related Iberian populations of 
<taxonomicName id="6EB142856607887E49A92E5138C126F1" genus="M." lsidName="M. serrulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="serrulatus">
<emphasis id="210C81E0510B9E2089A0647111E8C17E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. serrulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="59DE5F1522A921DCD3E326AE5C1A95AE" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Merodon serrulatus antenna. A outer side, lateral view, male (Spain) B inner side, lateral view, male (Spain) C dorsal view, male (Spain) D outer side, lateral view, female (Spain) E inner side, lateral view, female (Spain) F dorsal view, female (Spain) G outer side, lateral view, male (Greece) H inner side, lateral view, male (Greece) I dorsal view, male (Greece) J outer side, lateral view, male (Russia). Abbreviation: f-fossette. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377364" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">3B</figureCitation>
), molecular data and distribution (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="967B6EBD33F2B352B2789132A963ADEE" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of Merodon serrulatus species group." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377368" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">7</figureCitation>
). Related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C768E67325275FCABEB333DC6ED70F1" genus="M." lsidName="M. bequaerti" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis id="C0A4213AD740BAD86EE3657EFFBBFE0C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by shorter pile on ventral margin of metafemur in both sexes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C972E857DD848F663BDB480199F6AC41" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Metaleg, lateral view. A Merodon bequaerti, male B Merodon bequaerti, female C Merodon sacki, male D Merodon sophron, male. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377369" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">8D</figureCitation>
), narrower and oval to triangular apical part of anterior surstyle lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B1AEC0DE6F5B5DBC9B7C6582E6C45C18" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9G</figureCitation>
), with rounded margin in 
<taxonomicName id="BFA02AF30BBD82DDA4D77C269623CA10" genus="M." lsidName="M. bequaerti" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis id="7C144691FB833D6EA004BB716F90F4B0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6617DF6C89761E193EDE9DCFD3F1C2B9" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9A</figureCitation>
), and light yellow and less dense marginal pile on apical part of anterior surstyle lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2F6BBF56994298642846108DF332D514" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9G, K</figureCitation>
: al), dark brown and dense in 
<taxonomicName id="E4081ED861BE531D29FCE748CBBD233D" genus="M." lsidName="M. bequaerti" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="bequaerti">
<emphasis id="84E08506D05FB294C36FF325A2B4E02E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">M. bequaerti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="256EAD6F341DC62C2C50908EB48A5540" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9A</figureCitation>
: al, J).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="00DDB6AE1D0F36DAE3C149131A5D037C" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="redescription">
<paragraph id="06641687EEC600CBE61348F5FAC88BB6" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Redescription</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FB5437228EABB2C56970108A121A73F8" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
(based on the material from type locality, Middle Atlas, Azrou). 
<emphasis id="9192E24F8EC866CDA5EFD96419455DEA" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Male.</emphasis>
Head. Antennae black to dark brown; basoflagellomere elongated, ca. 1.8 times as long as wide, and ca. 2.5 times as long as pedicel, concave dorsally with acute apex; fossette dorsolateral; arista dark and thickened at basal one third, covered with dense microtrichia, ca. 1.8 times as long as basoflagellomere (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="993D6B36162D72B126AB7408CCD6D1F4" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Antenna. A Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon bequaerti, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, female D Merodon sacki, outer side, lateral view, male E Merodon sacki, inner side, lateral view, male F Merodon sacki, dorsal view, male G Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, male H Merodon sophron, inner side, lateral view, male I Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377372" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">11G, H</figureCitation>
); face and frons black with gray microtrichia, face covered with dense whitish, and frons with yellowish gray pile; oral margin shiny, with small lateral microtrichose area; lunule shiny black, bare; vertex shiny black, except in front of anterior ocellus, covered with microtrichia; vertex isosceles, with long, pale whitish yellow pile, mixed with black pile on the ocellar triangle; ocellar triangle isosceles; eyes covered with dense pile; occiput with gray-yellow pile, ventrally covered with a dense, gray microtrichia; eye contiguity 8-11 facets long; vertical triangle: eye contiguity: frons = 3: 1: 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BB364BD6B8AC23689145167965F9BFE" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Thorax. Scutum and scutellum black with bronze luster, covered with dense, erect, usually yellow pile; sides of scutum at wing basis with patch of black pile or fascia of short black pile and few black pile between wing basis; scutum with two microtrichose vittae, anteriorly connected and posteriorly reaching the scutellum; anterior half of scutum dull; posterodorsal part of anterior anepisternum, posterior anepisternum (except anteroventral angle), anterior anepimeron, dorsomedial anepimeron, and posterodorsal and anteroventral parts of katepisternum with long, dense pale yellow pile and grayish microtrichia; wings entirely covered with microtrichia; wing veins brown; calypteres and halteres pale yellow; legs mostly black, except brown tarsi ventrally in some specimens; pile on legs pale yellow; metafemur moderately incrassate, ca. three times longer than wide; pile on postero- and anteroventral surface 
<taxonomicName id="5FCC62CCC94491712BAEA7716A381677" genus="M." lsidName="medium" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="medium">medium</taxonomicName>
long, and ca. as one third of width of metafemur, approximately the same length as pile on dorsal surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C22C44E5003C6C92A426E3F03D8F4641" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Metaleg, lateral view. A Merodon bequaerti, male B Merodon bequaerti, female C Merodon sacki, male D Merodon sophron, male. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377369" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">8D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F80C386D67B0D4A36734948EB235ED43" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Abdomen. Tapering, 1.2 times longer than mesonotum; terga dark, except for a pair of pale yellow-orange, triangular, lateral maculae on tergum 2; terga 3 and 4 each with a pair of white microtrichose and oblique fasciae (on tergum 2 triangular); pile on terga all yellow; sterna dark brown, covered with long whitish yellow pile.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="507980E05C903E3E69FA457DC5828F96" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Male genitalia. Apical part of anterior surstyle lobe rhomboid shape, ca. 1.5 times longer than wide, covered with dense, short pile (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="180D20B6146A1337C88F5DD3C771F887" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9G, J</figureCitation>
: al); posterior surstyle lobe oval with basolateral protrusion (lateral hump) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D8CF0A36E1B82F3D1767572B252BBE79" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9G, H</figureCitation>
: bp); hypandrium sickle-shaped, without lateral projections; lingula 
<taxonomicName id="7FED0F774767CE989D6C31C0ABC7A07F" genus="M." lsidName="medium" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="medium">medium</taxonomicName>
size (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0ACDFF08AD16CF29B35CE56C63D89119" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Male genitalia. A Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, lateral view B Merodon bequaerti, epandrium, ventral view C Merodon bequaerti, hypandrium, lateral view D Merodon sacki, epandrium, lateral view E Merodon sacki, epandrium, ventral view F Merodon sacki, hypandrium, lateral view G Merodon sophron, epandrium, lateral view H Merodon sophron, epandrium, ventral view I Merodon sophron, hypandrium, lateral view J Merodon bequaerti, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view K Merodon sophron, anterior surstyle lobe, lateral view. Abbreviations: al-anterior surstyle lobe, bp-basolateral protrusion, l-lingula, pl-posterior surstyle lobe. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377370" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">9I</figureCitation>
: l).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="52E49F9B5A7D38856387FBC0F73D6F91" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis id="F254ABD610CBCBA55A67CBE79233168A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to the male except for normal sexual dimorphism and for the following characteristics: antennae with rounded tip, basoflagellomere ca. two times longer than wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C16DC83800EB939715DF819C6095C1CA" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Antenna. A Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, male B Merodon bequaerti, inner side, lateral view, male C Merodon bequaerti, outer side, lateral view, female D Merodon sacki, outer side, lateral view, male E Merodon sacki, inner side, lateral view, male F Merodon sacki, dorsal view, male G Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, male H Merodon sophron, inner side, lateral view, male I Merodon sophron, outer side, lateral view, female. Scale bar: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377372" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">11I</figureCitation>
); frons with broad microtrichose vittae along eye margins; frons covered with variable pilosity, from mostly gray-yellow until predominantly black; ocellar triangle covered with black pile; lateral side of terga, anterior two thirds of tergum 2 and all of tergum 5 with yellow pile; terga 2-4 with short adpressed black pile.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65690BCD32A8C17EE12FCB17A8E91FC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="543C486EB6D19092C69C8D70DBEB6EBC" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7378C0D3162B69E79ADE97D3EB1C03BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="994D4F385E783C7B8BF6724523748AC8" authorityName="Hurkmans" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Merodon sophron" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sophron">
<emphasis id="65F6CEAE5889A28377AA88F46C547BDC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Merodon sophron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed in north-western Africa (Morocco) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="342DE5D8F6072CD66E1CA822E082F351" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of Merodon serrulatus species group." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377368" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A294A07439DEAE156194FDA8E88D3442" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="C63F6904B6868BCF568977322997349D" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3058EE7D93E15F51FC6E3EA4A417FB49" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
Preferred environment: forest/open ground; open areas in evergreen oak maquis, dry 
<taxonomicName id="FF470556C8FFD3F474B6B806E2FD2C3C" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinus" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="94D97A09D8508C5CAB254955B252DA14" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forest; unimproved grassland and tracksides (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9532490220752709A259CB88A2525E80" captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Different types of habitats of Merodon serrulatus species group. A Lesvos (Greece), habitat of Merodon opacus sp. nov., Photograph by Ante Vujic B Siberia, Teletskoye Lake (Russia), habitat of Merodon serrulatus, Photograph by Jeroen van Steenis C Morocco, habitat of Merodon sophron, Photograph by Ante Vujic D Tajikistan, habitat of Merodon nigrocapillatus sp. nov., Photograph by Anatolij Barkalov." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.909.46838.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/377396" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">35C</figureCitation>
). Flowers visited: no data. Flight period: May-June.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
